  m_text: "Natalis VR is a virtual reality simulation designed for medical training,
    with a focus on maternity and delivery procedures. Developed by a team from Map\xFAa
    University, the project aims to provide an immersive, interactive, and hands-on
    learning environment where healthcare students and professionals can safely practice
    clinical skills. By combining realistic medical scenarios with VR hand tracking
    and interactions, NeoSim VR bridges the gap between classroom learning and real-world
    clinical practice."
